<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-08-22.1.mh" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa0822.htm">Scottish Executive</major-heading>

<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-08-22.2.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa0822.htm#1">Crime</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-08-22.2.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80116" speakername="Stewart Stevenson (Banff and Buchan) (SNP)" spid="S2W-27574" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa0822.htm#1">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what the detection rate was in 2005-06 for (a) theft and handling of stolen goods, (b) fraud and forgery, (c) criminal damage, (d) violence against the person, (e) sexual offences, (f) robbery and (g) all violent crimes.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-08-22.2.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80053" speakername="Cathy Jamieson" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa0822.htm#1">

  <p>This information will not be available until the publication, on 5 September 2006, of <em>Recorded Crime in Scotland, 2005-06</em> , a Scottish Executive National Statistics publication, which can be found at: <a href="http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Publications/2005/03/18798" target="_blank">http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Publications/2005/03/18798</a> .</p>

</reply>
